A Robot Handler is responsible for the setup, monitoring, and manual control of robotic systems during production, events, or demonstrations. They ensure the robot functions safely and efficiently, following pre-programmed sequences or real-time control inputs.

A Robot Programming Technician is responsible for configuring, testing, and maintaining robotic systems used in manufacturing, entertainment, or special effects environments. This role involves writing, debugging, and optimizing motion paths and logic routines to ensure safe and precise robot operation.

The Robot Supervisor oversees the operation, programming, and safety of robotic systems in live environments, production settings, or technical installations. They manage a team of operators and technicians to ensure the robots function as intended and meet performance standards.
